Cell["\<\
The sweep confirms a sporadic structure: most totals yield no solution, the \
small totals 8, 16 and 18 yield exactly one, and larger totals yield several \
(up to eight at S = 96). The parity plot makes the rule visible - every total \
with a solution is even - and the interactive view reconstructs the \
tetrahedron for any chosen total from its leg areas (x = Sqrt(2 A1 A2 / A3), \
and similarly for y and z).\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991453488220669*^9, 
  3.9914535215949135`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e2e652d1-cb94-274d-8e5d-\
f2ba85272d4c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"x", "=", 
  SqrtBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"2", 
     SubscriptBox["A", "1"], 
     SubscriptBox["A", "2"]}], 
    SubscriptBox["A", "3"]]]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9914535655580406`*^9, 3.9914536338330193`*^9}, {
  3.9914536911326313`*^9, 
  3.991453741106138*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"bcaccf09-2f0f-774a-beb3-\
01e5159260f3"],

Cell[BoxData[""], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.991453484241873*^9, 
  3.991480772649147*^9},ExpressionUUID->"6a3c8e0d-8c56-ae43-86e8-\
30762e7d6d15"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["6.3 Pattern: the total area is always even", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6943454921732183`*^9, 3.6943455118916535`*^9}, 
   3.694345567521351*^9, {3.9913003972172947`*^9, 3.9913003977861595`*^9}, 
   3.9914540063408356`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"66d7956e-b8c1-4f20-942d-\
92195bf5d549"],

Cell["\<\
The sweep reveals a clear structural property: a valid total area is always \
even. This follows directly from De Gua\[CloseCurlyQuote]s theorem. Since an \
integer and its square have the same parity (n^2 = n mod 2), the relation \
A4^2 = A1^2 + A2^2 + A3^2 gives A4 = A1 + A2 + A3 (mod 2). 
Therefore A1 + A2 + A3 + A4 = 2 (A1 + A2 + A3) = 0 (mod 2), so the total is \
always even. 
This explains why S = 18 can have a solution while odd neighbors such as 17 \
or 19 never can, and why no prime total (other than the too-small value 2) is \
ever achievable. 
The parity rule is the link between the sensitivity analysis and the \
generalizations discussed in Section 7.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6551323318137064`*^9, 3.655132346618133*^9}, {
  3.6558834788297663`*^9, 3.655883482105772*^9}, {3.655883581805547*^9, 
  3.655883589683561*^9}, {3.6558837346868153`*^9, 3.655883735919217*^9}, {
  3.694341574232729*^9, 3.694341596852769*^9}, {3.694342244717239*^9, 
  3.694342247462844*^9}, {3.694342333660995*^9, 3.694342343083412*^9}, {
  3.6943424202555304`*^9, 3.694342429299047*^9}, {3.6943424762647333`*^9, 
  3.694342484642213*^9}, {3.694342535512122*^9, 3.694342552269081*^9}, {
  3.6943425832578535`*^9, 3.694342597036641*^9}, {3.694342646046445*^9, 
  3.694342765915301*^9}, {3.694342880577859*^9, 3.694342892973568*^9}, {
  3.920005136849468*^9, 3.9200051373384686`*^9}, {3.9914540681238327`*^9, 
  3.9914541376487465`*^9}, {3.9914542177628574`*^9, 
  3.991454219596346*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"351a3f16-06d1-e046-a152-\
9222a45f5c1c"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Manipulate", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Module", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"sols", "=", 
        RowBox[{"solutionsForTotal", "[", "S", "]"}]}], ",", "parity"}], 
      "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"parity", "=", 
       RowBox[{"If", "[", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"EvenQ", "[", "S", "]"}], ",", "\"\<EVEN\>\"", 
         ",", "\"\<ODD\>\""}], "]"}]}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      RowBox[{"Column", "[", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"Style", "[", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"Row", "[", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
             
             RowBox[{"\"\<S = \>\"", ",", "S", ",", "\"\<  (\>\"", ",", 
              "parity", ",", "\"\<)  ->  \>\"", ",", 
              RowBox[{"Length", "[", "sols", "]"}], 
              ",", "\"\< solution(s)\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}], ",", "15"}], "]"}],
          ",", 
         RowBox[{"If", "[", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"OddQ", "[", "S", "]"}], ",", 
           RowBox[{"Style", "[", 
            
            RowBox[{"\"\<Odd total: impossible by the parity argument (always \
0 solutions).\>\"", ",", "Red"}], "]"}], ",", 
           RowBox[{"Style", "[", 
            RowBox[{"\"\<Even total: solutions may exist.\>\"", ",", 
             RowBox[{"Darker", "[", "Green", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], "]"}]}], "}"}],
        "]"}]}]}], "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"S", ",", "17", ",", "\"\<total area S\>\""}], "}"}], ",", "4", 
     ",", "60", ",", "1", ",", 
     RowBox[{"Appearance", "->", "\"\<Labeled\>\""}]}], "}"}]}], 
  "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9914541541718636`*^9},
 CellLabel->"In[11]:=",ExpressionUUID->"b00b0313-6960-794f-b284-eacaf87f4d20"],

